<title type="html"><![CDATA[Degrading SPR-RAM]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3157&amp;p=22878#p22878"><![CDATA[
Andrew Davie on the <!-- e --><a href="mailto:nesdev@yahoogroups.com">nesdev@yahoogroups.com</a><!-- e --> list stated that some prototypes of <em>The Three Stooges</em> were affected by this. Some revisions of the NES PPU would lose OAM data faster once the system warmed up, causing sprites to flicker. Spraying refrigerant on the PPU chip actually stabilized the sprites.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Apr 05, 2007 8:58 am</p><hr />
