<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3157&amp;p=22876#p22876"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Degrading SPR-RAM]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3157&amp;p=22876#p22876"><![CDATA[
It's DRAM; if each row of bits in the DRAM isn't accessed (refreshed) every so many milliseconds, the contents will deteriorate.<br /><br />When the screen is fully turned off, the PPU isn't refreshing the DRAM; if you plan to turn off the screen for long periods of time, be prepared to update OAM.<br /><br />(No damage to hardware)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Thu Apr 05, 2007 7:14 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
